  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nPapyrus\n\"For writing things\"\nObject Info\nPerk\nUsed to make Books among other things\n15 sec.\nCan be Burned\n40\nSource\n: ( ×1)\nDropped by\n:\nCrafting\n×4\nTab\nTier\nMiscellaneous\n\"papyrus\"\n“Some sheets of paper.”\n–Wilson\n“I bet it'd burn!”\n–Willow\n“Is like paper.”\n–Wolfgang\n“For documenting my pain.”\n–Wendy\n“I PREFER DOT MATRIX PAPER”\n–WX-78\n“Thin sheets of cellulose and lignin.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I'd rather chop than write.”\n–Woodie\n“A blank canvas.”\n–Maxwell\n“This paper has interesting clothlike properties.”\n–Wagstaff\n“This will carry förth the recörd öf my saga.”\n–Wigfrid\n“We could do our homework.”\n–Webber\n“Bet this burns good.”\n–Walani\n“I could write down my recipes on this.”\n–Warly\n“Aye! A fresh map!”\n–Woodlegs\n“WILBA CAN'ST BE POET NOW”\n–Wilba\n“Flat friends”\n–Wormwood\n“Dear Diary, today I made paper.”\n–Wheeler\n“I don't have much use for that, personally.”\n–Winona\n“An ancient scroll in the making.”\n–Wortox\n“Make more stories, Wicker-lady!”\n–Wurt\n“Just some paper with nothing on it.”\n–Walter\n“I should really write things down before I forget them...”\n–Wanda\nPapyrus, also known as Paper, is a Refined Item crafted with 4 Cut Reeds. A Science Machine is required to unlock the recipe. Papyrus can be used to make Honey Poultice for healing as well as a Birdcage, Night Armor, and Compass. Wickerbottom can use it to craft Books and starts out with two Papyrus. Papyrus can be used to fuel Campfires, though it has a low burn time.\nContents\n1 Downloadable Content\n2 Usage\n3 Trivia\n4 Gallery\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nIn the Reign of Giants and Shipwrecked DLCs, Papyrus is one of the ingredients to craft a Floral Shirt. Webber can use Papyrus to craft Spider Eggs.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×5\n×2\n×6\n×2\n×6\n×6\n×12\n×3\n×3\n×5\n×3\n×3\n×5\n×2\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nIn the old research system, the research cost of Papyrus was 30.\nDespite being made out of four Cut Reeds, Papyrus has the same burn time as one.\nPapyrus is a thin paper-like material made from the pith of Cyperus Papyrus, a species of reed native to Africa, also called the paper reed.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nOriginal HD icon from Bonus Materials from CD Don't Starve.\nResourcesCraftable Items\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items\nDSTDSRoGSWHam\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers & Stations\nRefined Materials\nWeapons\nArmor\nClothing\nHealing\nMagic\nDecorations\nStructures\nStorage Solutions\nCooking\nFood & Gardening\nFishing\nSeafaring\nBeefalo Riding\nWinter Items\nSummer Items\nRain Gear\nCrafting Station Filters\nSpecial Event\nAncient Pseudoscience\nCarpentry\nCartography\nCritters\nCelestial\nBrightsmithy\nShadowcraft\nFabrication\nBottle Exchange\nCombrining Filter\nTea Brewing Filter\nSculptures\nSeasonings\nTrading\nTrading Hutch\nOfferings\nCawnival Creation\nTrinket Trove\nMad Science\nWinter's Feast Cooking\nSanctum Smithy Filter\nCustom Course Shack Filter\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nAncient\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve: Reign of Giants Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nAncient\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Shipwrecked and Volcano Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nNautical\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nVolcanic\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Hamlet Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nTreasure Hunting\nSurvival\nNautical\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nGreen Thumb\nBooks\nTinkering\nCity Planning\nRenovate\nFloors\nShelves\nPlantholders\nColumns\nWall Papers\nHanging Lamps\nOrnaments\nChairs\nHome Kits\nDoors\nWindows\nRugs\nLamps\nTables",
